{
  "text": "where Q(s t , a t ) \u2286 P(S) is a closed bounded convex set of probability measures on S. In addition, when the conditional risk mapping satisfies the comonotonicity assumption [CITATION_1] , the set Q is polyhedral. The proposed algorithm can be, therefore, applied to any dynamically consistent risk measure in which the conditional risk mappings satisfy the comonotonicity assumption.",
